      <section eId="sec_CCP-561">
        <num>CCP 561</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-561__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Any formal discovery as authorized by this Code and served on all parties whether
or not filed of record, including the taking of a deposition with or without formal notice, shall
be deemed to be a step in the prosecution or defense of an action.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-561__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An appeal is abandoned when the parties fail to take any step in its prosecution
or disposition for the period provided in the rules of the appellate court.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112183</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
